name: First Electronic Bank
description: First Electronic Bank is an FDIC-insured, state-chartered industrial bank headquartered in Salt Lake City, Utah, regulated by the FDIC and Utah Department of Financial Institutions. With over 20 years of operating history and more than $6 billion in loans originated, the bank partners with fintech and financial services providers to offer credit products across the spectrumâ€”from prime to subprime lending, serving both individual consumers and small businesses. First Electronic Bank provides Banking-as-a-Service (BaaS) infrastructure for fintech partners including Visa, Mastercard, and American Express credit card issuance, revolving lines of credit, and closed-end loans. The bank works with leading fintech companies like Imprint and Cardless to issue co-branded credit cards for major retailers, airlines, and hotels.
